 2. Ontology / Triple Ingestion & Transformation Tools
These help convert, map, or pipe triples into a triplestore:

SemTK (Semantics Toolkit) — An open-source toolkit that allows users to convert CSV data into RDF triples and ingest them into a triple store, and also provides REST APIs for all functionality including data ingestion and queries. arxiv
Ontop / Ontopic Studio — Supports reasoning, RDF generation, SPARQL endpoints, and RDB-to-RDF conversion, directly usable from Java. W3C
J2RM — A tool to process mappings from JSON data to RDF triples guided by an OWL2 ontology structure. GitHub
ROBOT — A widely used ontology processing tool that can generate diffs, transform, and export ontology content in OWL/OBO formats for downstream ingestion.
